---
// The American Dream Was Real. Then They Broke It.
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-slate-50">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="section-line bg-red-500 mb-6"></div>
    <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-3xl md:text-4xl tracking-tight mb-3">
      The American Dream Was Real. Then They Broke It.
    </h2>
    <p class="font-body text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mb-10">
      You started your business because you believed in the promise: work hard, follow the rules, get ahead. That promise used to be true.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="card p-6 text-center">
        <div class="font-mono text-green-600 text-sm font-semibold mb-2">1940</div>
        <div class="stat-huge text-green-600">90%</div>
        <div class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mt-2">Of children out-earned their parents</div>
        <p class="font-body text-gray-600 mt-3">Work hard and you'd almost certainly do better.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card p-6 text-center">
        <div class="font-mono text-red-600 text-sm font-semibold mb-2">TODAY</div>
        <div class="stat-huge text-red-600">50%</div>
        <div class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mt-2">Of children out-earn their parents</div>
        <p class="font-body text-gray-600 mt-3">A coin flip. No matter how hard you work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card p-6">
      <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-4 text-center">
        What Changed?
      </h3>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-center">
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
          <div class="font-mono text-gray-500 text-xs mb-1">1976</div>
          <div class="font-bold text-gray-900">Top 1%: 10%</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">of income</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
          <div class="font-mono text-gray-500 text-xs mb-1">1980s</div>
          <div class="font-bold text-gray-900">Deregulation</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">begins</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
          <div class="font-mono text-gray-500 text-xs mb-1">2010</div>
          <div class="font-bold text-gray-900">Citizens United</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">unlimited $ in politics</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-xl">
          <div class="font-mono text-gray-500 text-xs mb-1">2024</div>
          <div class="font-bold text-gray-900">Top 1%: 20%+</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">of income</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-gray-700 text-center mt-6">
        As money in politics exploded, mobility collapsed and wealth concentrated at the top. <strong>Correlation isn't causation â€” but it's not coincidence either.</strong>
      </p>
      
      <p class="font-mono text-sm text-gray-400 mt-4 text-center">Raj Chetty, Harvard Opportunity Insights</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
